    "def draw_pca(X_r, y, target_names, ax, title):\n",
    "    lw = 2\n",
    "    colors = ['navy', 'turquoise', 'darkorange']\n",
    "    #[0,1,2] are three Names \n",
    "    for color, i, target_name in zip(colors, [0, 1, 2], target_names):\n",
    "        #draw 2 pca features for each y = target_names,3 species \n",
    "        ax.scatter(X_r[y == i, 0], X_r[y == i, 1], color=color, alpha=.8, lw=lw, label=target_name)\n",
    "    ax.legend(loc='best', shadow=False, scatterpoints=1)\n",
    "    ax.set_title(title)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, (ax1,ax2) = plt.subplots(2,1)\n",
    "draw_pca(X_r, y, target_names, ax1, 'PCA of IRIS dataset - 2 components variance ')\n",
    "draw_pca(X, y, target_names, ax2, 'Original IRIS dataset - full variance')\n",
    "fig.tight_layout()"
   ]

   "source": [
    "##Steps \n",
    "#0.0 MAINSTEP : Choose the right estimator \n",
    "lr = LogisticRegression(random_state=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "#1.0 Use Feature Extraction(for text/image data) - NA \n",
    "#1.1  Features selection , dimensionality reduction using sklearn.feature_selection or spark.ml.feature\n",
    "#1.2. Preprocessing steps eg StandardScaler, LabelEncoder from sklearn.preprocessing or StandardScaler, StringToIndex from spark.ml.feature\n",
    "iris = pd.read_csv('data/iris.csv')\n",
    "iris.head()\n",
    "y_raw = iris.Name \n",
    "X = iris.iloc[:,0:4].astype(np.float64)\n",
    "X.shape, y_raw.shape\n",
    "\n",
    "lenc = LabelEncoder()\n",
    "y = lenc.fit_transform(y_raw)\n",
    "#X side \n",
    "std = MinMaxScaler()\n",
    "#X1 = std.fit_transform(X)\n",
    "sel = SelectKBest(chi2, k=2)\n",
    "#X2 = sel.fit_transform(X1,y)\n",
    "#2. Split data into training and test data \n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X,y, random_state=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "#3. Combining various steps  - Use Pipeline in both sklearn and spark-ml\n",
    "pipeline = Pipeline([('sc', std),('sel', sel),('lr', lr)])\n",
    "\n",
    "#4. Train - fit on training data and then predict on test data (sklearn)/ transform(spark-ml) \n",
    "#and  Evaluate model performance on test data (sklearn.metric) or BinaryClassificationEvaluator,  \n",
    "#MulticlassClassificationEvaluator,  RegressionEvaluator from spark-ml\n",
    "pipeline.fit(X_train,y_train)\n",
    "print('Train score', pipeline.score(X_train,y_train),  #uses internaly one metric, ->1 Best\n",
    "     'Test Score', pipeline.score(X_test,y_test))\n",
    "#Train score 0.9553571428571429 Test Score 0.9473684210526315\n",
    "scores = cross_val_score(pipeline, X, y, cv=10)\n",
    "print(scores, \"\\nAvg:\", scores.mean(), \" +/- \", scores.std())\n",
    "y_pred = pipeline.predict(X_test)\n",
    "print(\"prediction for X_test\", y_pred, \"\\nTrue value:\", y_test)\n",
    "#5. Select best parameter using GridSearchCV/RandomizedSearchCV  or CrossValidator in spark-ml\n",
    "#Tune C=regParm = [0.1,1,10], k=[1,2,3]\n",
    "params = dict(lr__C=[0.1, 1.0, 10.0], sel__k=[1,2,3]) #indentifierDOUBLEUNDERSCOREhyperparam\n",
    "gs = GridSearchCV(pipeline, params)\n",
    "gs.fit(X_train,y_train)\n",
    "print(\"best Model\", gs.best_estimator_,\n",
    "     \"\\nTrain Score\", gs.score(X_train,y_train),  #uses internaly one metric, ->1 Best\n",
    "     'Test Score', gs.score(X_test,y_test))\n",
    "scores = cross_val_score(gs, X, y, cv=10)\n",
    "print(scores, \"\\nAvg:\", scores.mean(), \" +/- \", scores.std())\n",
    "y_pred = gs.predict(X_test)\n",
    "print(\"prediction for X_test\", y_pred, \n",
    "      \"\\nwith reverse transform:\", lenc.inverse_transform(y_pred))"
   ]
